column115: There has NEVER been any tornado warning system in our County. We rely on the Weather Channel when we are home and a storm is approaching. In the event a thunderstorm would occur during the night hours that prompted a tornado warning it is very likely we would never know unless we were awakened and had enough time to view the TV and that is why I said we would do nothing even in a 100% chance. I often wondered if the county could blow the local fire siren in such an event.
I hope I read the question correctly. Four dollars for a new system that would work like you described is a minimal investment for each person in the United States Good luck

Les sugerimos que tambien tomen medidas para atras ocasiones huracanes, teremotos, etc. Somos personas positivas tratando de vivir en paz y armonia. Y tratar de servir en los momentos dificiles que nos ha tocado en estos momentos. Bendiciones!!

While I believe the new warning system could be helpful, I believe it also could become less effective due to the "future time intervals" and the chances of a tornado happening in said area. We all know the actual occurrence of a tornado happening is difficult enough to forecast/predict.  It is in my opinion that the meteorologists at the NWS and forecasters at the SPC are the best in the business.  I just wish more people paid attention to the weather, especially when severe weather is being predicted at some times, 4+ days in advance!  The current system is sufficient in today's time.  If anything, I wish the government would upgrade the radars to a more modern technology.  It is my belief, that this upgrade would provide better lead times and possible better understandings on why certain storms produce tornadoes and some don't.   Thank you for all of the hard work you do day in and day out!

column71: Monitor the direction and speed then shelter at home if danger is imminent

column115: “Shelter at home” is a bit too vague. There’s a difference between staying in my basement, watching the radar, and going down into the cellar.
